body_html:
I have recently updated to tensorflow 12.1 and installed tflearn.!
I had the same problem when using batchnormalization from tflearn.
I followed @suiyuan2009's suggestion and changed the tf. ones_initializer to tf.ones_initializer()
and the error is gone (changing tf.zeros_initializer to tf.zeros_initializer() would generate error! so I left it as is)
Now I'm getting
AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'control_flow_ops'
any idea how to fix this?

body:
I have recently updated to tensorflow 12.1 and installed tflearn.!
I had the same problem when using batchnormalization from tflearn. 
I followed @suiyuan2009's suggestion and changed the `tf. ones_initializer` to `tf.ones_initializer()`
and the error is gone (changing `tf.zeros_initializer `to `tf.zeros_initializer()` would generate error! so I left it as is)
Now I'm getting 
`AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'control_flow_ops'`
any idea how to fix this?
